Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place green beans in a 9x13 inch glass pan. Saute onions with butter in a large frying pan over medium heat until translucent. Add flour and stir to coat flour. Gradually add milk and bring to a boil. Add cheese, sour cream, sugar, and salt. Cook till thickened and cheese is melted. Pour mixture over green beans and top with a layer of stuffing. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.